The measure of angle $ACB$ is 40 degrees. If ray $CA$ is rotated 480 degrees about point $C$ in a clockwise direction, what will be the positive measure of the new acute angle $ACB$, in degrees?

[asy]
draw((0,0)--dir(40),linewidth(1),Arrow);
draw((0,0)--dir(0),linewidth(1),Arrow);
dot(.8dir(40));
dot(.8dir(0));
dot((0,0));
label("A",.8dir(40),NW);
label("B",.8dir(0),S);
label("C",(0,0),W);
[/asy]

Suppose $\sin N = \frac{2}{3}$ in the diagram below.  What is $LN$?



[asy]
pair L,M,N;
M = (0,0);
N = (17.89,0);
L = (0,16);
draw(L--M--N--L);
draw(rightanglemark(L,M,N,18));
label("$M$",M,SW);
label("$N$",N,SE);
label("$L$",L,NE);
label("$16$",L/2,W);
[/asy]

